					<article>
						<h4>Risk Management and Clearances</h4>
						<p>
							On January 1, 2015 the changes in the PA Child Protective
							Services Act went into effect. These changes are a dramatic
							change from the previous version of the law and require we
							all make changes to how we approach protecting the children
							in our organizations. PA West Soccer can no longer provide
							a clearance through a third party source and therefore has
							discontinued offering an eKidsafe clearance. We have made
							adjustments to our system so it will help us manage the
							documents required by the new law.
						</p>
						<p>
							Please read this document from Tim McCoy on how the
							Pennsylvania law changes affect PA West referees:

							<a href="#">Risk Management Changes</a>.
						</p>
					</article>
					<article>
						<h4>Unanchored Goals</h4>
						<p>
							It's referee's responsibility to make sure players are safe.
							The first priority when arriving at a field is determining if
							it's fit to play on.  Failing to perform this duty is a
							significant breach of the Referees's responsiblies, and could
							result in players getting injured. 
						</p>
						<p>If goals are not anchored, do not start the game!</p>
